s://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132609314,imgsize-775778.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[In 2015, trees covered just 1.9% of these Ethiopian drylands; nine years later...]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132608491.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a span of nine years, Ethiopia's drylands have observed significant forest expansion alongside a reduction in soil erosion. The practices of assisted natural regeneration and active tree planting have been pivotal in enhancing forest density. As a result, severe topsoil loss in the mountainous terrain has meaningfully diminished. These outcomes resonate with Ethiopia's ecological objectives and green economy initiatives, underscoring practical approaches for restoring ravaged communal landscapes.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/in-2015-trees-covered-just-1-9-of-these-ethiopian-drylands-nine-years-later-helping-old-roots-regrow-pushed-forest-cover-above-22/articleshow/132608491.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/in-2015-trees-covered-just-1-9-of-these-ethiopian-drylands-nine-years-later-helping-old-roots-regrow-pushed-forest-cover-above-22/articleshow/132608491.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-24T20:41:21+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132609101,imgsize-133158.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Korean professor who got his students to write a research paper for his daughter's admission to a top dental school sent to jail for 3.6 years]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132608665.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes